But - your knowledge seems to be quite limited if you have the supposition that an MKG can not be a RT representation of the enterprise. An MKG, when federated with the contextually associated time series through a single GraphQL API and managed microservices effectively becomes a single schema. Because the queries that comprise this API can be subscribed to - all clients (UI and other microservices) post and calculate RT views of the enterprise to all nodes in the system, including the edge.

Second - GraphQL is the API over the top of the MKG. Everything between the plant floor and the MKG is MQTT. All interop between system functions and external sources are managed by microservices.

