@Luke Smaul Flipping that, I’d say…
Automating the integration of systems (OT-IT), with accessible equipment object models and custom mapping of data necessary to do that, are necessary precursors to widespread digital transformation.

Quoting @js, “Consumers are not buying frameworks or semantic model standards. They're buying products.”
The “highly-customized and highly-engineered deployments (i.e., code on operating systems)… manufacturers should be subsidizing and Azure, AWS, SAP, Siemens, Rockwell, etc. should be paying for the last mile. With the current approach, there's no chance of adoption [of OPC-UA or other object models] anytime soon. It's just too cost prohibitive.”

The fact that neither of those is happening---that technical debt and risk-averse industries work in opposition to it happening---describes the greater opportunity right now for OEMs, integrators and engineering firms with vision to be disruptive.
