@chris.demers here's what our Solutions Architect and former CTO of PackIoT, Mario Ishikawa had to say on this.

Mario Ishikawa
I'd say it will depend of the size, but there is always a need to have a champion driving it. However, in several cases the champion won't have the political capital, so this champion should not be the one trying to convince the board. Instead, the vision should come from the board, from the CEO, and this champion should be then chosen and empowered. A lot of departments need to work together in harmony despite of divergent goals they already might have. I like the book Digital Transformation, by Thomas Siebel, who address this. In short, small companies can have this being driven by the CEO or someone designated by her/him for it. For larger companies, for a unified and receivable plan by all plants and departments there should be someone from C-level fully involved on this. What we usually see is a VP of Digital Transformation.

